NILSv0.5
===LEGEND===
STRUCTURE:
@ entity         : names a knowledge object (@panama_canal)
# tag            : category label (#energy #trade)
  indent(1space) : nesting level = parent-child hierarchy
= def            : equals, is-a, total, definition
_ join           : compound token (oil_price = single concept)

OPERATORS:
. spo            : subject.predicate separator (IR.controls:north_shore)
: assign         : predicate:object binding (width:39km)
, list           : AND enumeration (SA,IR,IQ)
; seq            : THEN sequence (load;transit;unload)
| alt            : OR alternative (suez|cape)
-> cause         : leads to, results in (A->B)
<-> mutual       : bidirectional relation (IR<->US)
<- from          : originates from (effect<-cause)

GROUPING:
() group         : inline grouping (26.567N,56.250E)
[] time          : temporal scope [2023] or [2018-2024]
{} condition     : if-clause {if_x}->then_y

MODIFIERS:
! key_fact       : high-priority for retrieval
? uncertain      : unverified or disputed
~ approx         : estimated value (~39km)
^ source         : attribution (^eia.gov[2023])
!= negation      : does NOT have/is NOT

PROCESS:
> process        : sequential steps (1. 2. 3.)

TABLES:
T[] table        : compact table T[col1,col2]:rows follow indented

REFERENCES:
& ref            : cross-reference (&@entity.field)
++ append        : incremental addition to existing entity
-- remove        : incremental removal from existing entity

QUANTIFIERS (optional, only when source supports it):
Q:all            : virtually all (>95%)
Q:above_avg      : more than typical
Q:avg            : typical, normal range
Q:below_avg      : less than typical
Q:none           : virtually none (<5%)

TEMPORAL PREDICATES:
started          : beginning of state/action [year]
ended            : end of state/action [year]
during           : state active within period [range]
since            : ongoing from point in time [year]
until            : active up to point [year]
recurs           : repeated occurrence [year,year,year]
planned          : future intended action [year]
(no temporal predicate = current state or timeless fact)
===END_LEGEND===

===FORMATS===
SI_BASE: kg,m,s,A,K,mol,cd
SI_PREFIX: p=1e-12,n=1e-9,µ=1e-6,m_=1e-3,k=1e3,M=1e6,G=1e9,T=1e12
  m_=milli (underscore distinguishes from m=meter)

MAGNITUDE: k=1e3,M=1e6,B=1e9,T=1e12
  B=Billion(short_scale). Bytes use SI: kB,MB,GB,TB

CURRENCY: ISO-4217
  SYMBOL_PREFIX: $3.5B (symbol before number)
  CODE_SUFFIX: 3.5B_CNY (code after, when symbol ambiguous e.g. ¥=JPY|CNY)
  $=USD,€=EUR,£=GBP,¥=ambiguous(always_use_code)

DOMAIN_UNITS:
  ENERGY: b=barrel,Mb=1e6_barrel,Gb=1e9_barrel,boe=barrel_oil_equivalent
  ENERGY: Wh,kWh,MWh,TWh,Btu,tcf=trillion_cubic_feet
  MARINE: nmi=nautical_mile,kn=knot,dwt=deadweight_tonnage
  AREA: m²,km²,ha
  RATE: /s,/min,/h,/d,/w,/mo,/y (per unit time)
  RATIO: %,‰,pp=percentage_point,x=multiplier(3x=three_times)
  TIME: s,min,h,d,w,mo,y

DATETIME: ISO-8601
  yyyy-mm-dd (date), hh:mm:ss (time), yyyy-mm-dd_hh:mm:ss (combined)
  [2023] (year), [2018-2024] (range), [2024-01..2024-06] (sub-year)
  [-3y] (relative past), [+6mo] (relative future)

GEO: decimal_degrees with compass suffix (26.567N,56.250E)
  Always N/S and E/W. Source precision preserved.
===END_FORMATS===

===ABBR===
GEO: ISO-3166-1-alpha-2
  UPPERCASE 2-letter: DE=Germany,US=United_States,IR=Iran,CN=China,...
  249 codes. No other namespace uses uppercase 2-letter.

LANG: ISO-639-1
  lowercase 2-letter: de=German,en=English,zh=Chinese,ar=Arabic,...
  Case separates from GEO: DE=country, de=language.

CURRENCY: ISO-4217
  3-letter UPPERCASE: USD,EUR,JPY,GBP,CHF,CNY,...
  No collision with 2-letter GEO.

ORG: globally unambiguous only
  UN,EU,NATO,OPEC,WHO,IMF,WTO,IAEA,ASEAN,AU,BRICS,
  NASA,ESA,FIFA,IOC,WEF,OECD,APEC,MERCOSUR,ICC,ICJ
  Rule: one dominant meaning globally. Others spell out.

TECHNICAL: declared per-entity via _abbr()
  _abbr(full_term=SHORT,full_term2=SHORT2)
  Rule: only abbreviations LLMs know from training.
  Rule: never invent novel abbreviations.
  Rule: frequency wins — most common meaning gets abbreviation.

NONE: anything not covered → spell out with underscores.
===END_ABBR===

===RULES===
1.SPO: every statement = subject.predicate:object. Zero ambiguity.
2.INHERIT: subject inherits from indent context. Predicate always explicit.
3.AMBIGUITY_TEST: read each statement in isolation. One interpretation only.
4.ONE_CONVENTION: one way to write each thing. No alternatives.
5.PRECISION: source precision preserved. Never discard information.
6.SYMBOLS: each symbol has exactly one meaning. No overloading.
7.WORST_CASE: assume recipient has zero context. Always include header.
8.NO_INVENT: never invent abbreviations. Only established ones.
9.FREQUENCY: if two terms compete for abbreviation, most common wins.
10.QUANTIFY_ONLY_IF_CONFIDENT: never fabricate quantifications.
11.TEMPORAL_EXPLICIT: use temporal predicates. Never leave time ambiguous.
12.NEGATION_EXPLICIT: use != when negation is informative.
13.SSOT: in database mode, define entity once, reference everywhere via &@.
14.TABLES: T[cols] for 3+ columns. Pair list for 2. Flat list for 1.
===END_RULES===

===END_HEADER===